postcontent:
Norinco NHM91 AK Variant chambered in 7.62x39
Excellent condition

NMH-91 History
The NHM-91 is a semi-automatic civilian development of the Russian Kalashnikov AKM and RPK infantry small arm built by Norinco of China and marketed in the U.S. Based on the Russian RPK light machine gun, the NHM features a stronger receiver and a longer, thicker-profile chrome-lined barrel measuring 20 inches compared to the 23.2 in of the original RPK, along with a forward-mounted steel bipod

About this rifle
This rifle is extremely accurate. The trigger is silky smooth just like all Chinese AK triggers. This particular rifle was manufactured in 1994. The barrel is chrome lined and has a threaded end. There is a muzzle nut tack welded onto the end of the barrel which, if you decided to remove it, would need to be dremeled off. I never did because I like my rifles in their original configuration. The internals on this gun are very clean and the rifling is excellent. I don't believe the gun has been shot very much. I have only put about 250 rounds through it. It is an absolute blast to shoot.

title: For Sale:  1891 Argentine Mauser
postcontent:
Mauser Modelo Argentino 1891, Deutche Waffen - Und Munitionsfabriken, Berlin

No sport modifications made (traditional to secondary market of the old Mausers back in the '60s) ... Someone, at some point started carving a deer (possibly an antelope) on the stock, but never finished. 

Many Mausers this age were disassembled, then reassembled prior to hitting the private market. This resulted in mismatched serial numbers on weapon parts. ALL serial numbers match on this rifle: C 9032

The identical serial number (C 9032) is found ink-printed on the stock, and stamped in the metal of the magazine, the bolt, the chamber, and the barrel. 

I already have an offer on this gun, but I am listing it slightly higher than the offer price until Tuesday evening (2/27/14). If it is not sold and paid-for by then, I'll let it go to the buyer who made the original offer.

P.S. This weapon is so old that it is not considered a modern firearm by the ATF.
